<subSubSection id="6EDC654FFE41FF8AFF32FD8F5E1AFC8C" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph id="267936C4FE41FF8AFF32FD8F58F8FDCC" blockId="1.[174,1232,577,827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Widespread in North and South Europe, North Africa. Oriental Region; Middle East: 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE41FF8AFE95FDAF5D95FDCC" box="[324,467,609,635]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE41FF8AFE0CFDAF5E75FDCC" box="[477,563,609,635]" name="Turkey" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE41FF8AFDECFDAF5EF6FDCC" box="[573,688,609,635]" name="Mongolia" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE41FF8AFD6BFDAF5EA8FDCC" box="[698,750,609,635]" name="Iran" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Iran</collectingCountry>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFD26FDAF5FFDFDCC" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[759,955,608,635]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref6810" refString="Rozkosny, R. 1987. A review of the Palaearctic Sciomyzidae (Diptera). Biologia 86. Prirodovedecka Fakulta, Univerzita J. E. Purkyne, Brne, 1 - 100." type="book chapter" year="1987">Rozkošný (1987)</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFC17FDAF58FDFDCC" author="Knutson, L. V. &amp; Shagudian, E. R. &amp; Sahba, G. H." box="[966,1211,608,635]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="145 - 155" refId="ref6445" refString="Knutson, L. V., Shagudian, E. R., Sahba, G. H. 1973. Notes on the biology of certain snail-killing flies (Sciomyzidae) from Khuzestan (Iran). Iranian Journal of Public Health, 2 (3), 145 - 155." type="journal article" year="1973">Knutson et al. (1973)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE41FF8AFF32FD4F5E1AFC8C" blockId="1.[174,1232,577,827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">
Biology. Larvae are predators as well some terrestrial (
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE41FF8AFC50FD4F580BFD2C" authorityName="H. B. Baker" authorityYear="1925" box="[897,1101,641,667]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haplotrematidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Haplotrematidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE41FF8AFB8BFD4F588AFD2C" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[1114,1228,641,667]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Helicidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE41FF8AFF7FFD6E5D7AFD0C" authorityName="Pilsbry" authorityYear="1895" box="[174,316,672,699]" class="Gastropoda" family="Polygyridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Polygyridae</taxonomicName>
) as freshwater gastropods (
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE41FF8AFD51FD6F5F52FD0C" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[640,788,673,699]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Lymnaeidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE41FF8AFCF0FD6F5FCBFD0C" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1833" box="[801,909,673,699]" class="Gastropoda" family="Physidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Physidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE41FF8AFC48FD6E586AFD0C" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[921,1068,672,699]" class="Gastropoda" family="Planorbidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Planorbidae</taxonomicName>
), and also the hygrophilous 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE41FF8AFE80FD0F5EFCFD6C" authority="(Bratt et al., 1969)" baseAuthorityName="Bratt" baseAuthorityYear="1969" box="[337,698,704,731]" class="Gastropoda" family="Succineidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">
Succineidae (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFE3DFD0F5EF4FD6C" author="Bratt, A. D. &amp; Knutson, L. V. &amp; Foote, B. A. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[492,690,704,731]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 247" refId="ref5863" refString="Bratt, A. D., Knutson, L. V., Foote, B. A., Berg, C. O. 1969. Biology of Pherbellia (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). New York Agricultural Experiment Station of Ithaca Memoirs, 404, 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1969">Bratt et al., 1969</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Firstly, 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFCCCFD0F5FA2FD6C" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[797,996,704,731]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="117 - 160" refId="ref6777" refString="Rozkosny, R. 1967. Zur Morphologie und Biologie der Metamorphosestadien mitteleuropaischer Sciomyziden (Diptera). Acta Academiae Scientiarum, Brno, 1 (4), 117 - 160." type="journal article" year="1967">Rozkošný (1967)</bibRefCitation>
described the larval and puparial stages. As 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE41FF8AFE15FD2F5FCFFD4C" authority=", Bratt et al. (1969)" authorityName="Bratt" authorityYear="1969" box="[452,905,736,763]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grisescens">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE41FF8AFE15FD2F5EE9FD4D" box="[452,687,737,763]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Pherbellia grisescens</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFD6CFD2F5FCFFD4C" author="Bratt, A. D. &amp; Knutson, L. V. &amp; Foote, B. A. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[701,905,736,763]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 247" refId="ref5863" refString="Bratt, A. D., Knutson, L. V., Foote, B. A., Berg, C. O. 1969. Biology of Pherbellia (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). New York Agricultural Experiment Station of Ithaca Memoirs, 404, 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1969">Bratt et al. (1969)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
described the entire life cycle and detailed all the immature stages. The puparium is formed inside the host snail, and overwinters there (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE41FF8AFE5AFCEF5E16FC8C" author="Bratt, A. D. &amp; Knutson, L. V. &amp; Foote, B. A. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[395,592,800,827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 247" refId="ref5863" refString="Bratt, A. D., Knutson, L. V., Foote, B. A., Berg, C. O. 1969. Biology of Pherbellia (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). New York Agricultural Experiment Station of Ithaca Memoirs, 404, 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1969">Bratt et al., 1969</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
